timeline.bodyText:
Can we not use nested/chained ternaries? YMMV, but I find them hard to read. Might be improved with linebreaks in different places, but I think an if-else is easier on the eye (if a little more verbose):
TemporalAccessor value;
if (label.startsWith("--")) {
    value = DASH_FORMATTER.parse(label);
} else if (label.length() >= 8 && label.charAt(2) == ':' ) {
   value = OFFSET_TIME_FORMATTER.parse(label);
} else {
  value = DATETIME_FORMATTER.parse(label);
}
or perhaps more clean:
final TemporalAccessor value = getFormatter(label).parse();

... 

private static DateFormatter getFormatter(String label) {
    if(label.startsWith("--")) {
       return DASH_FORMATTER;
   } 
   if (label.length() >= 8 && label.charAt(2) == ":") {
       return OFFSET_TIME_FORMATTER;     
   }
   return DATETIME_FORMATTER;
}

